Description: Fragrances are created from essential oils present in plants, flowers, fruits, barks, roots, and animal secretions. And what precious pricey substances they are! In Grasse, France, the centre of the World Perfumery Industry, workers rise early to pick Jasmine before dawn. When the sun peeks over the horizon, the flower loses twenty percent of its aroma. A skilled harvester can pick about a pound of flowers in forty five minutes, or five thousand tiny blossoms. But only a few drops of essence will emerge after processing. Eight hundred pounds of Jasmine flowers, or four million flowers, yield just one pound of concentrated oil. And the price of the essences? One pound of this oil, called Jasmine Absolute will fetch from 80,000 to 1, 00,000, depending on quality, while Rose Absolute can cost as much as 2,50,000 to 3,00,000 per pound.

The dry down notes of cedarwood and labdanum leave a signature trail of the Mediterranean.

Title: United Colors Of Benetton By Benetton For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray 4.2-Ounces
Description: He lives for the rush of adrenaline that pumps through his veins as he crosses the finish line far ahead of the herd. He trains and works towards that one moment, biding his time and making good all the promises he made to himself. As the finishing tape breaks, he gets high on his own heady success; Benetton Sport is a luxury fragrance that pays its respects to this iron-willed man. A citrusy burst of lime, lemon and wild mint leaves makes for fresh opening notes for the Eau de Toilette along with clementine and grapefruit to balance the fragrance. The heart hides a concoction of cyclamen, geranium and sweet ginger blossom which rests on a base of cedar, sandalwood, oak, vetiver and biomusk. Benetton Sport was launched in 2001 and has found its niche among discerning audience who relish the blast of freshness that the fragrance exudes. The tall, sleek black flacon which encloses the fragrance seems to epitomize the quintessential sportsman; let the power of Benetton Sport course through your veins as you reach the pinnacle, unaided and unopposed.
